<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="installvsgrid">
      <title>Virtuoso ADO.Net Data Grid Form Application</title>
      <para>This section details the steps required to create a simple Visual Studio 2008 Windows Form
application with associated DataGridView control for displaying data in selected tables from a Virtuoso
database.</para>
      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>Launch the Visual Studio 2008 SP1 IDE.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg1" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Visual Studio</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg1.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Create a Web Application project by going to the File menu in Visual Studio and choosing New Project.
  </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>When the New Project window appears, choose either Visual Basic or Visual C# as the programming language.
  </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Within the language category, click on Windows and select Windows Form Application from the right-hand panel.
  </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Choose a name for the project, for example VirtuosoDataGridApp, and click OK.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg5" floatstyle="1">
            <title>name for the project</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg5.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>From the Data, menu select the Show Data Sources menu item to display a list of available Data sources.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg6" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Show Data Sources</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg6.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Click on the Add New Data Source link to add a new data source.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg7" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Add New Data Source</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg7.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>In the Data Source Configuration Wizard dialog  Choose Data Source Type page, select the Database data source type and click Next.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg8" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Data Source Configuration Wizard</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg8.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>In the Data Source Configuration Wizard dialog Choose your Data Connection page, select the New Connection button.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg9" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Data Connection page</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg9.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>In the Choose Data Source dialog, select OpenLink Virtuoso Data Source from the list and click Continue.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg10" floatstyle="1">
            <title>OpenLink Virtuoso Data Source</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg10.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>In the Add Connection dialog, specify the hostname, portno, username, and password
for the target Virtuoso Server and check the Save Password check box.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg11" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Add Connection dialog</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg11.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Select the Select Database From List radio button and choose School from the drop down list
of available databases.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg12" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Select Database From List</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg12.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Click the Test Connection button to verify the connection is successful and then
click OK to add the connection.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg13" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Test Connection</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg13.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Select the  Yes, include sensitive data in the connect string radio button and click Next to continue.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg14" floatstyle="1">
            <title>connect string</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg14.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>In the Choose your Database Objects dialog select the table and columns to be queried, the shippers table is used in this example.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg15" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Choose your Database Objects</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg15.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>A DataSet for the shippers database object is created
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg16" floatstyle="1">
            <title>shippers database</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg16.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>From the drop down list box next to the Shippers table ensure the DataGridView item is selected
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg17" floatstyle="1">
            <title>DataGridView</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg17.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Drag the Shippers DataSet item onto the Form to create a scrollable and editable association of the Shippers table object with the Data Grid View automatically.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg18" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Drag</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg18.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>From the Debug Menu select the Start Debugging menu item to run the application.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg19" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Debug</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg19.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>The data in the Shippers table will be displayed in the DataGrid application created.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg20" floatstyle="1">
            <title>DataGrid</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg20.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>A new row can be inserted (updated or deleted) as indicated for the new DHL record inserted below and the  save button clicked to save the change to the database.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg21" floatstyle="1">
            <title>new row</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg21.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>The Virtuoso Interactive SQL tab of the Conductor can be used to run the query select * from Demo..Shippers.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg22" floatstyle="1">
            <title>Interactive SQL tab</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg22.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>To verify the change has been successfully made in the database.
    </para>
          <figure xml:id="insg23" floatstyle="1">
            <title>verify</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ui/insg23.png"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
      <para>The task is now complete.</para>
    </section>
